The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Another SA controversy 
Durban: South African cricket is headed towards another racial controversy following a fax circulated ahead of the annual meeting of the UCBSA in Johannesburg this weekend. The fax contains names of new board of directors for Cricket South Africa Ltd omitting UCBSA president Ray Mali and CEO Gerald Majola, the two black members. It names vice-president Roy Kurz as new chairman of the board of directors of this commercial arm of UCBSA along with Mahomed Jajbhay and Brandon Foot as vice-chairman and CEO, respectively. (PTI)  Copyright 
